Vice President Mike Pence recently held a phone call with members of the American Camp Association to discuss the safe reopening of summer camps amid the COVID-19 pandemic. The Vice President, along with White House Coronavirus Response Coordinator Dr. Deborah Birx, discussed best practices and resources provided by the American Camp Association and the CDC for youth and summer camps. Assistant Secretary of the Treasury Michael Faulkender also provided an update on the Paycheck Protection Program, clarifying that seasonal employers like camps can access forgivable loans. The Vice President thanked the participants for their commitment to children and for following guidelines to safely open their camps this summer.